metadata.name: Fauvist and the Gray Men
metadata.description:
The gray men look outside their cubicle and see a being that's wild, full of life, and surrounded by the beauty of the world. They see an individual. They're curious and they observe. The wild being is an Artist. They are not concerned with the cubicle of the gray men...they enjoy the beauty around them.

Artist: Rain Spann  
Title: "How Should Life Look?  
Size: 2519px by 3226px 
DPI: 300  
Materials: Oil pastel, ink, acrylic, and graphite on paper then scanned

-"You only need one wing to fly"
